Karabo Ngoepe, News24Pretoria - Former Proteas cricket player Herschelle Gibbs is expected to appear in the Cape Town Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday on a drunken driving charge.The appearance comes after Gibbs missed his last court sitting, allegedly because he was not in the country.Gibbs was arrested after he was allegedly involved in a collision in Camps Bay. No one was injured in the crash, but Gibbs was allegedly speeding when he crashed into a Toyota.Gibbs was charged with reckless driving in 2009 after an accident in Seapoint, but the case was withdrawn.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.